<br>
Threads posted on this board are subject to scrutiny and criticism.  If someone wants to argue that the sky isn't blue, that is their right, no matter how ridiculous they may sound.  If I happen to disagree with a post, and I feel like posting, I'll let you know it.  But, I'm not going to start a thread and then tell those that disagree with me that they don't deserve to be there (not saying that's what Danzin is doing here).<br>
<br>
Anyway, back on topic.  I can't seem to get my point across, which is my fault.  Sometimes my mind won't slow down enough for me to say what I actually mean.  But what I meant by Gorebelly admitting to killstealing is this: what is your definition of killstealing?  Some people call it that when an individual or group takes over a camp that someone else already had been camping for awhile.  Or by pulling a mob from someone else's camp.  Or by killing a mob that someone else says they were triggering.  None of this is killstealing, but people have described it as such.  Now, if Gorebelly admitted to killing the AC after it had already been engaged, thats one thing.  But, if he only admitted to killing the AC that someone else was &quot;camping&quot;, then that's another.  Just like people to be sure of themselves when trashing someone else.<br>
<br>
